etymologies: late 19th century. From ancient Greek νήπιος infant, child (of uncertain origin) + -onic

definitions: Designating the early postembryonic stages of ontogeny, specifically the stage between the embryonic and the neanic; of, relating to, or at such a stage of development.

notes.text: Applied variously in different groups of organisms, but especially to the earliest stage of shell growth in molluscs.
